2 2 8, and (E K )
4 4 4 at pH 7 and 2 wt % with 0 mM added NaCl. Solid lines indicate the Debye form factor fits for a Gaussian coil and the dashed lines indicate where dimensionless q2Rg2·I(q)/I(0) = 1.1 and qR 3
g= for a globule conformation. These can be used as reference for evaluating degree of polyampholyte collapse.
